Jasmine virus H (JaVH) is a novel virus associated with symptoms of yellow 
mosaic on jasmine. The JaVH genome is 3,867 nt in length with five open reading 
frames (ORFs) encoding a 27-kDa protein (ORF 1), an 87-kDa replicase protein 
(ORF 2), two centrally located movement proteins (ORF 3 and 4), and a 37-kDa 
capsid protein (ORF 5). Based on genomic and phylogenetic analysis, JaVH is 
predicted to be a member of the genus Pelarspovirus in the family Tombusviridae.

